  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AL-02 sensitivity gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across five flow-speed operating points and a verbal screening sensitivity study is referenced in the UQ narrative; however, no structured hasSensitivityAnalysis link is encoded, leaving the dominant input drivers uncharacterized. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels, supporting an Accepted decision. The missing sensitivity-analysis linkage constitutes the W-AL-02 aleatory sensitivity gap.",
