      "rationale": "SST k-omega and realizable k-epsilon compared against PIV; SST k-omega selected based on superior near-wall velocity agreement. Giersiepen hemolysis power-law validated against Wurzinger shear-exposure dataset. Achieved level equals required level.",
      "note": "A verbal screening sensitivity study comparing hemolysis model coefficients is cited in the UQ narrative (see hasUncertaintyQuantification), but no structured sensitivity analysis artifact is linked to this package. The dominant input drivers—power-law exponent and shear stress threshold—remain uncharacterized in the evidence record."
