      "rationale": "Twelve uncertain inputs (viscosity, density, hemolysis power-law exponent, inlet velocity profile parameters, wall roughness, and others) assigned log-normal or normal distributions from literature meta-analysis. Monte Carlo propagation uses 15,000 Latin hypercube samples. A screening sensitivity study is mentioned in the UQ report narrative as having been conducted to rank inputs, but the study is not formally linked as a structured sensitivity analysis record in this package; consequently the relative contribution of each input to output variance is not traceable from the evidence record alone. Achieved level equals required level.",
      "uqNarrative": "Monte Carlo UQ (15,000 LHS samples) propagates twelve input uncertainties through the CFD hemolysis model. The UQ report narrative references a one-at-a-time screening study performed prior to the full MC run, identifying the hemolysis power-law exponent and exposure-time integration step as potentially influential; however, this screening was not formalized into a sensitivity analysis artifact and is not linked here. The 95th-percentile NIH prediction interval is 0.0041–0.0089 mg/dL, remaining below the clinical threshold of 0.012 mg/dL."
