    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors achieve levels meeting or exceeding required levels for MRL 5. Monte Carlo UQ demonstrates that the 95th-percentile NIH prediction interval remains below the clinical threshold with margin. GCI below 5% confirms discretization error is controlled. Validation NRMSE of 9.4% is within the 15% acceptance criterion. The assessment team notes that a screening sensitivity study was referenced verbally in the UQ narrative but was not submitted as a structured evidence artifact; this gap was considered acceptable given the overall margin demonstrated by the MC interval, and the decision proceeds as Accepted pending formal sensitivity analysis documentation in a subsequent submission.",
